					<td background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/trick.jpg" width="100%" valign="top">


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Wizard Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:Fire_Mage15@hotmail.com">Malfoy</a> | 
		            2/28/2000 4:46:27 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I'm only lvl 17,but i will tell you what i know (from the view as a wizard the qeynos area),here it goes:(NOTE:if an erudite,[which i personaly recommend for the great base int.] go strait over to qeynos on the boat,and find a kind person to bind you)<BR>
<BR>
LEVEL 1-3: after getting your basic spells and equipment,use your practice points mainly for channel and evoc. don't worry about saving them for later.  save 1 or 2 for piercing or 1h blunt. don't bother w/ armor and just get teh basic spells,u can skip the lvl 1 bolt spell,but get the AE. around lvl 2-3 i would attack 3separate snakes,and use the ae spell to get quick exp(worked great)<BR>
<BR>
LEVEL 4-8:<BR>
<BR>
at 4,hunt the fire beetles outside of qeynos gate..just be carful not to get TOO many after you at a time.  At 5,head to the everfrost ent. to Black Burrow and hunt the weaker gnolls out there  At 6 you can move into BB and hunt the scrawny gnolls or stay out of BB and keep w/ the weaker gnolls(this tends to be safer because of the lack of trains) Level 7 i found to be a terrable lever because the snakes are too hard and the gnolls give pretty iffy exp and all you have is a 14dd spell!  DO NOT DESPAIR! just try to get to 8 and you will be set.  Root is the necesity for these levels! although my personal methods don't use it much now..i still relied on heavily at my 1-12 levels.<BR>
<BR>
8-11:<BR>
FINALLY! now that you have some decent spell..you can take the snakes in bb. until 11. buy both the 34dd and 45dd spells..be careful w/ you fire spell,being a bolt..u have to be careful as to not to zap and hit the sloping groud. at 11 you can group with a tank and take the 2elite gnoll guard and gnoll spawn up on the ledge.<BR>
<BR>
12-15:<BR>
ahh...the infamous shock of lightning! yes this does around 80dmg for 60mana,and you will love it!  This is when i went out to the tundra to kite! yes..we wizards can kite,and even better than druids in some ways!there are 2 ways to kite w/ a wizard:1st way is to root and blast away,after 2zaps or so,root again and keep it up. 2nd(and prefered by me) is to get a sow from your neighborhood shaman or druid and zap,run,zap,ect. until your target dies! if need be,you can also death kite(god forbid)[for all you who do not know how this works,you run ahead,med until you see your mana go up a spurt,run ahead again,med for a spurt,repeat until you can zap.]at about 14 i left for east karana,but the tundra can still supply decent exp.<BR>
<BR>
16-19:<BR>
ah...triple digit zaps..very nice..being a wizard..believe it or not..you can kite a crag spider(lvl 18-20)!  Although this may require death kiting, you can still do it..just make sure you are not poisened,as this can be a killer doing 240 loss of hp.  basially you can just kite crags and undead reavers for great exp.  if you tend to want a bit of social life,(even the hardened wizzies need to talk once in a while)you can form a group and take crags.<BR>
<BR>
20 and on...:<BR>
<BR>
now you have the personal tele spells,although the lvl 20 are pretty basic, at 24 you get 5 new ones that are a nice addition.<BR>
at 20 you recieve the ~200dd spell! this is an all or nothing spell with a slight chance of being resisted.  the 20's are where the wizzies start to shine.  if you have made it this far,kudos to you for making it through the hard times!  Now w/ your high dmg zaps, depending on how much you play,you can make it from 20 to 30 in a week or a month(which is quite speedy indeed!) eventually you will have to group because of the inability of soloing,but you will be very valued for the ability to nuke, teleport,and seek out the area ahead w/ you sight spells. and the ability to teleport to alternate planes is also nifty.  good luck to all you future blasters of Norrath!<BR>
<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
