				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In my oppinion of leveling in Qeynos as a Erudite Wizard i have found that level 7 is not tough. i am there now and have discovered two things that help to rectify the long level. <BR>
<BR>
1:Fight rabid things wolfs or bears IF you can take them. dont worry too much about the disease but dont neglect it as well. you can get it cured by either a druid, cleric OR when you turn in the diseased pelts for GOOD exp at level 7 five diseased wolf pelts plus the wolf kills gave me almost a full bubble of experience. <BR>
<BR>
2:Fight gnolls and COLLECT the gnoll fangs turn them in to the captain in the arena, upstairs on the left?.  give them to him in ONE at a time collect the four moonstones and trade them in for more exp and even more money 5x more than selling the moonstones. dont remember who though, look it up on this site. 8 fangs finished the last sliver of 6 and gave me a little more than a full bubble in 7.<BR>
<BR>
Just though i'd help make level 7 a little easier for everyone.<BR>
<BR>
Thendar, Erudite wizard.
